SIMPLE: insincerity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insincerity
<hw>In`sin*cer"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>insinc⟦eacute⟧rit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being
insincere; lack of sincerity, or of being in reality what one appears to
be; dissimulation; hypocritical; deceitfulness; hollowness;
untrustworthiness; <as>as, the <ex>insincerity</ex> of a professed
friend; the <ex>insincerity</ex> of professions of
regard.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What men call policy and knowledge of the world, is commonly no
other thing than dissimulation and <qex>insincerity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insinew</ent>⟦br⟧
